# Cypress + Next.js Streaming

When a route has a `loading.tsx` (Suspense boundary), the skeleton HTML arrives before the server component content streams in. Cypress `cy.visit()` resolves on the `load` event, which fires during the skeleton — **not** after streaming completes.

## After navigating to a page, always wait for streamed content

Assert on an element that only exists in the **real** page, not the skeleton, before interacting.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — URL changes while skeleton is still showing
cy.visit(`/app/applications/${id}`)
cy.contains('button', /acciones/i).click()

// ❌ BAD — URL updates before content streams in
cy.findTableRow('25,000').find('a').click()
cy.url().should('match', /\/app\/applications\/\d+/)
cy.contains('button', /acciones/i).click()

// ❌ BAD — applicant name exists on BOTH the list and detail page;
// matches stale list-page DOM before the skeleton replaces it
cy.findTableRow('25,000').find('a').click()
cy.contains(applicant.name).should('be.visible')
cy.contains('button', /acciones/i).click()

// ✅ GOOD — guard on content UNIQUE to the destination page
cy.visit(`/app/applications/${id}`)
cy.contains('h1', /detalle de solicitud/i).should('be.visible')
// Wait for the element you'll interact with; content may stream in chunks
cy.contains('button', /acciones/i).should('be.visible').click()
```

## Wait for element before clicking (reduce flakiness)

Always chain `.should('be.visible')` before `.click()` on buttons, links, and menu items. Cypress will retry until the element is in the DOM and visible, then click.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — wait then click
cy.contains('button', /guardar/i).should('be.visible').click()
cy.get('[role="menuitem"]').contains('Autorizar').should('be.visible').click()
cy.findTableRow(name).find('button[aria-label="Asignar empresas"]').should('be.visible').click()
```

## After actions that cause redirect or reload

Server actions that call `redirect()` or same-URL redirect cause a full page load. Wait for the new page before asserting or interacting.

1. **Redirect to a different URL** (e.g. form submit → list): wait for `cy.url().should(...)`, then wait for a **stable element on the new page** (e.g. `cy.get('table').should('be.visible')` or `cy.get('main').should('be.visible')`), then assert on specific content.
2. **Redirect to the same URL** (e.g. status update → same detail page): the page reloads and may stream. Wait for the **page shell** first (e.g. `cy.contains('h1', /detalle de solicitud/i).should('be.visible')`), then wait for the **new state** (e.g. `cy.contains(/autorizado/i).should('be.visible')`).
3. **After navigating to a list** (e.g. click "Back"): wait for the list to be ready (`cy.get('main').find('table').should('be.visible')`) before `findTableRow` or row assertions.

```typescript
// After status update (same-URL redirect)
cy.get('[role="menuitem"]').contains('Autorizar').should('be.visible').click()
cy.contains('h1', /detalle de solicitud/i).should('be.visible')
cy.contains(/autorizado/i).should('be.visible')

// After form submit → list (different URL)
cy.contains('button', /guardar/i).should('be.visible').click()
cy.url().should('include', '/app/companies')
cy.get('table').should('be.visible')
cy.contains(newCompany.name).should('exist')
```

## Prefer positive assertions over negative ones for async actions

After a server action (form submit, dialog confirm), assert the **next expected state** rather than the absence of the previous state.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — races against animation + server action latency
cy.contains('button', /confirmar/i).click()
cy.get('[role="dialog"]').should('not.exist')

// ✅ GOOD — retries until the new state appears
cy.contains('button', /confirmar/i).click()
cy.get('[data-status="rejected"]').should('be.visible')
```
